** Your key accountabilities **

** The core capability requirements for this role are: **

• Manage a team of subject matter experts in the design, procurement,
implementation, support and maintenance of ICT systems.  
• Undertake research and analysis on new and emerging technological trends and
products which may impact upon the ICT systems and provide innovative
solutions for continual improvement.  
• Always ensure the integrity of ICT system, in particular the capture and
retention of lawfully detected information and the security of evidence files.  
• Build and maintain communication networks with internal and external clients
and stakeholders and provide high level advice on technical related issues.  
• Develop business requirements and specifications to facilitate vendor
quotations, and subsequently, manage budgets, contracts and deliverables.  
• Implement strategies to identify, assess and mitigate risks.

** Role Requirements **

** Technical/ Operational/ Educational experience **

Highly Desirable

• Prior experience in an enterprise-scale ICT environment.  
• Experience designing, implementing, supporting and maintaining mission
critical 24x7 ICT services.  
• Experience administering server and desktop technologies, including but not
limited to Linux - Ubuntu/Debian Desktop and Server, VMWare ESX Server,
vSphere, MS Windows Server 2008/2012/2019, and Windows 10  
• Experience administering networking technologies for complex ICT systems
using tools such as Untangle Firewall and SquidVPN and experience conducting
security risk assessments, and business impact analysis with these systems.  
• Experience administering digital forensics software such as LACE, Nextcloud,
GriffEye and Cellebrite.  
• Experience in troubleshooting and solving technical issues.  
• ITIL 4 Foundation

Desirable

• A tertiary qualification in Information Technology or related discipline  
• Project management skills  
• Organisational change management experience  
• Relevant industry accreditations and certifications

** Special Conditions **

This position maybe required to:

• Participate in a 24x7 on-call ICT support roster.  
• Undertake periodic pre-approved overtime and periodic work outside normal
business hours.  
• Provide expert evidence on ICT systems related matters on behalf of the
Queensland Police Service (QPS) in a Court of Law.

